<item>
            <title>[LU-9606] When and Where can I get the ldiskfs which support Linux kernel 4.1 or later?</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9606</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am studying Lustre 2.9 and need rebuild it in the Linux kernel 4.1.38. But the ldiskfs code I can get only support kernel 3.12 or earlier.&lt;br/&gt;
In the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9240&quot; title=&quot;Can the ldiskfs support Linux kernel 4.1.38+?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9240&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9240&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Mr Dilger said this project is in progress, and Mr Simmons said the SLES12SP2 can support the 4.4 kernel.But I can&apos;t receive any more messages from them.&lt;br/&gt;
So I create this question and hope anyone who knows can tell me: 1, When and where can I get the ldiskfs which support kernel 4.1 or latter. 2, How can I get the Lustre source support SLES12SP2. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
